description: A breakfast frittata recipe with simple ingredients but packed with aroma and savoury flavour.
name: Herb Baked Frittata Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 1 small red onion, peeled and diced

recipeInstructions.text: Heat up a 9 inch skillet or similar oven proof pan to a medium heat and then fry the onions and herbs for 5 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, lightly beat the eggs with the milk and add the salt and pepper.
Pour the egg mixture into the skillet and mix well with the onion and herbs.
Allow the eggs to cook on the skillet for 5 minutes and then cover with grated cheddar cheese and place in the oven for 10 minutes.
Once the edges and top start to brown, remove from the oven and allow to set for 3 minutes before serving.
